and create apps that integrate speech seamlessly for all who need or want it.","type":"text"}],"sampleCodeDownload":{"kind":"sampleDownload","action":{"type":"reference","identifier":"https:\/\/developer.apple.com\/videos\/play\/wwdc2020\/10022","isActive":true,"overridingTitle":"Watch Video (8 min)"}},"references":{"WWDC20.jpeg":{"identifier":"WWDC20.jpeg","type":"image","variants":[{"url":"\/images\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC20.jpeg","traits":["1x","light"]}],"alt":null},"doc://WWDCNotes/documentation/WWDCNotes/WWDC23-10033-Extend-Speech-Synthesis-with-personal-and-custom-voices":{"role":"sampleCode","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Bring the latest advancements in Speech Synthesis to your apps. Learn how you can integrate your custom speech synthesizer and voices into iOS and macOS. We’ll show you how SSML is used to generate expressive speech synthesis, and explore how Personal Voice can enable your augmentative and assistive communication app to speak on a person’s behalf in an authentic way."}],"type":"topic","kind":"article","url":"\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/wwdc23-10033-extend-speech-synthesis-with-personal-and-custom-voices","identifier":"doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC23-10033-Extend-Speech-Synthesis-with-personal-and-custom-voices","title":"Extend Speech Synthesis with personal and custom voices"},"doc://WWDCNotes/documentation/WWDCNotes/WWDC20":{"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Xcode 12, Swift 5.3, iOS 14, macOS 11 (Big Sur), tvOS 14, watchOS 7."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"New APIs: "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"WidgetKit"},{"type":"text","text":", "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"StoreKit Testing"},{"type":"text","text":", and more."}],"role":"collectionGroup","type":"topic","title":"WWDC20","identifier":"doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC20","images":[{"identifier":"WWDC20-Icon.png","type":"icon"},{"identifier":"WWDC20.jpeg","type":"card"}],"kind":"article","url":"\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/wwdc20"},"WWDC20-Icon.png":{"type":"image","identifier":"WWDC20-Icon.png","alt":null,"variants":[{"url":"\/images\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC20-Icon.png","traits":["1x","light"]}]},"https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2020/10022":{"type":"download","checksum":null,"url":"https:\/\/developer.apple.com\/videos\/play\/wwdc2020\/10022","identifier":"https:\/\/developer.apple.com\/videos\/play\/wwdc2020\/10022"},"https://wwdcnotes.com/documentation/wwdcnotes/contributing":{"identifier":"https:\/\/wwdcnotes.com\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/contributing","type":"link","title":"Learn More…","titleInlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Learn More…"}],"url":"https:\/\/wwdcnotes.com\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/contributing"},"doc://WWDCNotes/documentation/WWDCNotes":{"images":[{"type":"icon","identifier":"WWDCNotes.png"}],"type":"topic","kind":"symbol","role":"collection","title":"WWDC Notes","url":"\/documentation\/wwdcnotes","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Session notes shared by the community for the community."}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes"},"WWDCNotes.png":{"variants":[{"url":"\/images\/WWDCNotes\/WWDCNotes.png","traits":["1x","light"]}],"type":"image","alt":null,"identifier":"WWDCNotes.png"},"doc://WWDCNotes/documentation/WWDCNotes/WWDC18-236-AVSpeechSynthesizer-Making-iOS-Talk":{"kind":"article","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Speech can enhance the audio experience of your app, whether you are generating spoken feedback for accessibility, or providing critical information beyond simple alerts or notifications. AVSpeechSynthesizer produces synthesized speech from text and allows you to control and monitor the progress of ongoing speech. Learn the ins and outs of AVSpeechSynthesizer and how to add computer-generated speech output to your app."}],"role":"sampleCode","type":"topic","identifier":"doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC18-236-AVSpeechSynthesizer-Making-iOS-Talk","url":"\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/wwdc18-236-avspeechsynthesizer-making-ios-talk","title":"AVSpeechSynthesizer: Making iOS Talk"},"doc://WWDCNotes/documentation/WWDCNotes/WWDC19-248-Creating-an-Accessible-Reading-Experience":{"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"The styling and layout of text is a hallmark feature of an outstanding reading experience. Technologies such as CoreText and TextKit give you the tools you need to create a great text layout. Learn how to make an equally great accessible experience for VoiceOver by adopting the accessibility reading content protocol, adding automatic page turning, and customizing speech output."}],"url":"\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/wwdc19-248-creating-an-accessible-reading-experience","kind":"article","type":"topic","identifier":"doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC19-248-Creating-an-Accessible-Reading-Experience","role":"sampleCode","title":"Creating an Accessible Reading Experience"}}}